<keyLead id="812E9595F46BFFD33CC8FCA235E4BA87" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
4. Small, from 
<quantity id="FD279B45F46BFFD33D11FCA23279BA64" box="[334,513,842,865]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6149999999999998" metricValueMax="1.67" metricValueMin="1.56" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="16.15" valueMax="16.7" valueMin="15.6">15.6 to 16.7 mm</quantity>
. Orbicular spot absent in some specimens and in other represented as a swelling of the antemedial line (
<figureCitation id="A2E42A25F46BFFD33D26FC8231C0BA84" box="[377,440,874,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[275,1305,212,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-177@4.[270,1316,197,1659]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Adults of Bergiantina, schausi group. 1. B. schausi, dorsal view; 2. B. schausi, ventral view; 3. B. intermedia, dorsal view; 4. B. intermedia, ventral view; 5. B. parva, dorsal view; 6. B. parva, ventral view; 7. B. trita, type, dorsal view; 8. B. dolens, type, dorsal view. Natural Size 1:1." pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
